<html><head></head><body><b>William Thomson, Lord Kelvin of Largs (1824–1907)</b><br/>
A renowned British physicist and inventor, author of studies on thermodynamics. He took particular interest <br/>in obtaining low temperatures <br/>and in the condensation <br/>of gases, formulated the Law <br/>of Conservation of Energy and the Second Law <br/>of Thermodynamics, <br/>and proposed an absolute scale of temperature.</body></html>